  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-03 18:54 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC reclaim persists, ecb6 above 5M\n\n**Task:** Verify whether the BTC bullish reclaim persisted after the 18:24 upgrade, focusing on BTC net staying above `$17M`, `beatmaker1` holding long, `anon-0x8fcc` rebuilding toward `$5M`, and cross-asset divergence.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Fresh tracker output: **BTC 8L/0S**, **ETH 1L/6S**, **SOL 3L/5S**.\n- Current top-book notional: BTC **+$19.06M net long**, ETH **-$34.15M net short**, SOL **-$10.87M net short**, HYPE **-$10.59M net short**, JTO **+$355 net long only**.\n- BTC reclaim persisted and strengthened vs 18:24: count improved from **7L/0S** to **8L/0S**, net improved from **+$18.74M** to **+$19.06M**, and visible BTC shorts remain **$0**.\n- `anon-0xecb6` BTC LONG rebuilt from **$4.47M** to **$5.12M**, now above the clean `$5M` anchor for this trader.\n- `beatmaker1@proton.me` still holds BTC LONG **$2.46M** after flipping from short earlier.\n- `anon-0xfc66` BTC LONG steady at **$5.63M**; `anon-0x57dd` BTC LONG increased slightly to **$1.52M**.\n- Remaining BTC caveat: `anon-0x8fcc` is still unchanged at **$4.30M LONG**, below the preferred **$5M** anchor.\n- ETH remains high-conviction bearish: **1L/6S**, net **-$34.15M**, with `anon-0x3bca` ETH SHORT still **$1.41M**.\n- SOL remains bearish by notional, count contested: **3L/5S**, net **-$10.87M**.\n- HYPE remains bearish by count and notional: **2L/7S**, net **-$10.59M**.\n- JTO top-trader confirmation remains absent.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p1-btc-reclaim-persists-ecb6-above-5m-2026-05-03-1854.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** BTC is now more than a one-refresh bounce. Net has held above `$17M` across consecutive P1 checks, visible shorts remain flushed, and `ecb6` rebuilt above `$5M`. The only reason not to call this fully clean is that `8fcc` remains stuck at `$4.30M` instead of rebuilding near/above `$5M`. The combined book is still divergent: BTC is bullish-reclaim/near-clean, while ETH/SOL/HYPE remain heavily bearish.\n\n**Decision:** Upgrade BTC from **bullish reclaim with caveat** to **BTC bullish / near-clean**, with the remaining `8fcc` caveat. Full clean bullish requires either `anon-0x8fcc` near/above **$5M** or one more refresh with BTC net **>$17M** and no shorts. Distribution trigger reinstates if BTC net falls below **$15M**. Hard downgrade remains BTC net **<$10M** or `anon-0x8fcc` flips short above **$2M**. Keep ETH bearish confidence high. Keep SOL bearish by notional, count contested. Keep HYPE bearish confidence high. Keep PM weekend block active; no Sunday exception. Keep HL live notional-blocked; no forced trades from `$37.39`. Do not treat JTO P3 momentum as copy-intel confirmed.\n\n**Next:** Watch whether `anon-0x8fcc` finally rebuilds toward **$5M** and whether BTC stays **8L/0S**. If BTC remains >$17M with no shorts one",
